      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Understood. No goblins, no magic, just straight-to-the-point professional communication. Here is a standard, empathetic template for an HR manager to send a rejection email to a final-stage candidate.\n\n***\n\n**Subject:** Update Regarding Your Application for [Job Title]\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you for taking the time to interview with us. We truly appreciate the opportunity to meet with you and learn more about your background.\n\nAfter reviewing all the candidates who applied, we have decided to move forward with [Name of the new candidate] for this position. While we are proud of [Candidate Name]'s qualifications, we believe they are the best fit for our current team's specific needs at this time.\n\nPlease know that this decision is not a reflection of your worth or the quality of your skills. We value your interest in our company and hope you will find this outcome inspiring.\n\nWe wish you the best in your future endeavors and hope to have the opportunity to work with you again in the future.\n\nSincerely,\n\n[Your Name]\n[Your Title]\n[Company Name]",
      "source": "target",
